$ Shell command: basename
@ basename

`basename` prints the trailing part of a filesystem path. Optionally, it can remove a suffix as well.

{ Print last part of path

  gh|shell-commands|/basename/remove-directory||

}
{ Remove last part of path and optionally remove suffix

  gh|shell-commands|/basename/remove-directory-and-suffix||

}
sa:

  → Linux/shell/commands[Shell commands] such as `→ Linux/shell/commands/dirname`

  → development/languages/Perl/modules/File/Basename
